\", \"Yverdon-Les-Bains\", \"Z\u00fcrich, Part 1\", \"Z\u00fcrich, Part 2\"\n|-\n|2012\n| ''Clayton Grange''\n|Saunders\n|\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Neverwhere#Radio|Neverwhere]]''\n| Mr Croup\n|\n|-\n|2018\n|[[The Archers]]\n|Robin Fairbrother\n|\n|}\n\n===Stage===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 1985-1986\n| ''Yonadab''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://theatricalia.com/play/5em/yonadab/production/by1 |title=Production of Yonadab |author=<!--Not stated--> |date= |website=Theatricalia |publisher= |access-date=14 October 2018}}</ref>\n| Absalom\n|\n|-\n| 1990-1991\n| ''[[The Rocky Horror Show]]''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thestage.co.uk/features/interviews/2015/anthony-head-were-the-only-artists-in-the-world-who-dont-practise/ |title=Anthony Head: 'We're the only artists in the world who don't practise'\n\n |author=David Hutchison|date=11 October 2015 |website=[[The Stage]]|publisher= |access-date=14 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n| Dr. Frank N. Furter\n| As part of the 1990-91 West End revival production at the [[Piccadilly Theatre]]\n|-\n| 1994\n| ''[[Rope (play)|Rope]]''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/theatre-murder-most-horrid-paul-taylor-finds-chilling-parallels-in-keith-baxters-production-of-1369744.html|title=THEATRE / Murder most horrid: Paul Taylor finds chilling parallels in Keith Baxter's production of Patrick Hamilton's Rope at Wyndham's\n\n |author=Paul Taylor|date=13 April 1994 |website=[[The Independent]]|publisher= |access-date=14 October 2018}}</ref>\n| Rupert Cadell\n|\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[Otherwise Engaged]]''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2005/nov/01/theatre|title=Otherwise Engaged\n\n |author=[[Michael Billington (critic)|Michael Billington]]|date=1 November 2005 |website=[[The Guardian]]|publisher= |access-date=14 October 2018}}</ref>\n| Jeff Golding\n\n| Directed by Simon Curtis, also starring [[Richard E. Grant]] and [[David Bamber]]\n|-\n| 2010\n| '