{"title_page": "Merrell Twins", "text_new": "{{short description|YouTube personalities}}\n{{Infobox YouTube personality\n|name = Merrell Twins\n|image = Merrell-twins-gesf-2018-7824-large.jpg\n|caption = Veronica and Vanessa Merrell at the 2018 [[Global Education and Skills Forum]]\n|birth_name = Veronica Jo Merrell<br />Vanessa Jo Merrell\n|birth_date = {{birth date and age|1996|08|06}}\n|birth_place = [[Kansas City, Missouri|Kansas City]], [[Missouri]], U.S.\n|nationality = American Mexican Irish Italian Jewish Christians morning is that the beast I did last time with the day you got your birthday \n|residence = [[Simi Valley]], [[California]], U.S.\n|occupation = [[YouTube]] personalities, actresses, musicians\n|height_ft=5|height_in=2|height = \n|website=https://www.merrelltwins.com|channel_name = merrelltwins\n|channels=|years_active = 2009\u2013present\n|subscribers = 5.35 million subscribers\n|subscriber_date = April 9, 2020\n|views = 1 billion views\n|view_date = February 9, 2020\n|silver_button = Yes\n|silver_year = 2014\n|gold_button = Yes\n|gold_year = 2016\n}}\n\n'''Veronica Jo Merrell''' and '''Vanessa Jo Merrell''' (born August 6, 1996), known as the '''Merrell Twins''', are identical twin American [[YouTube]]rs, actresses, and musicians. Hey sorry if we did a lot going in and the snow is fine brutality is your the way I can get you to do\n\n==Personal lives==\nThe Merrell Twins are identical twin sisters born in [[Kansas City, Missouri]] on August 6, 1996.<ref name=\"people\">Gomez, Patrick. [http://people.com/celebrity/jane-the-virgin-and-youtubes-the-merrell-twins-5-things-to-know/ \"5 Things to Know About Jane the Virgin and YouTube's Merrell Twins\"]. ''People''. December 13, 2015.</ref> Veronica \"Roni\" is 45 minutes older than Vanessa \"Nessa\". They grew up in Kansas City before moving to [[Greater Los Angeles]], California in June 2013 at the age of 16 to pursue a career in acting.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Twersky |first1=Carolyn |title=9 Hilarious Insider Facts About the Merrell Twins |url=https://www.seventeen.com/celebrity/a26591977/merrell-twins-facts/ |website=Seventeen |accessdate=6 February 2020}}</ref> They also had a very short time with [[Disney Channel]].<ref name=\"variety\">Spangler, Todd. [https://variety.com/2016/digital/news/vanessa-veronica-merrell-youtube-tv-show-1201797408/ \"Vanessa & Veronica Merrell: Twins Win Social Fans and Angle for TV Show\"]. ''Variety''. June 21, 2016. Retrieved September 18, 2017.</ref>\n\n==Career==\nThe Merrell Twins started making YouTube videos in 2009.<ref>Gavilanes, Grace. [http://people.com/celebrity/the-merrell-twins-youtube-stars/ \"Shorty Award Nominees The Merrell Twins on Their Lives as Famous YouTubers: 'It's Made Us More Confident'\"]. ''People''. April 11, 2016. Retrieved September 18, 2017.</ref> Their videos are produced and edited by their father, Paul Merrell.<ref name=\"variety\"/> They regularly appear in [[AwesomenessTV]] videos and had recurring roles on the television show ''[[Jane the Virgin]]''.<ref name=\"variety\"/> They appeared in the 2016 film ''The Standoff''. In 2016 at the [[8th Shorty Awards]], they won for [[YouNow]]er of the Year.<ref name=\"8th_Shorty\">[http://shortyawards.com/8th/merrelltwins \"ABOUT MERRELL TWINS]. Shortyawards.com. Retrieved September 18, 2017.</ref>\n\nThey won a [[Streamy Award]] for Best Live Social Media in 2016.<ref name=\"2016Streamy\">{{cite news |last1=Spangler |first1=Todd |title=Streamy Awards 2016: Full Winners List |url=https://variety.com/2016/digital/news/streamy-awards-2016-winners-list-1201878399/ |access-date=August 13, 2018 |work=Variety |date=5 October 2016}}</ref> In 2017, they were nominated for Choice Female Web Star at the [[Teen Choice Awards]].<ref name=\"TCA2017\" /> In 2018, they were nominated for two [[Teen Choice Awards]]: Choice Female Web Star and Choice YouTuber.<ref name=\"EONLINE2018\">{{cite news |last1=Johnson |first1=Zack |title=Teen Choice Awards 2018 Winners: The Complete List |url=https://www.eonline.com/news/956235/teen-choice-awards-2018-winners-the-complete-list |access-date=August 13, 2018 |work=E! Online |date=August 12, 2018}}</ref> They won the [[8th Streamy Awards|2018 Streamy Award]] in the Lifestyle category.<ref name=\"2018Streamy\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/lists/streamy-awards-2018-winners-list-1146664/item/kids-family-1146634|title=Kids and Family \u2013 Streamy Awards 2018: Winners List|work=The Hollywood Reporter|access-date=2018-10-24|language=en}}</ref> \nIn July 2018, the Merrell Twins released their clothing line, True IMG. The phrase \u2018true image\u2019 is derived from the meaning of Veronica\u2019s name, and its logo features a butterfly dotting the \u2018I\u2019 in IMG referring to the meaning of Vanessa\u2019s name in Greek.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Weiss |first1=Geoff |title=The Merrell Twins To Launch \u2018True Img\u2019 Fashion Brand Tomorrow |url=https://www.tubefilter.com/2018/07/16/merrell-twins-true-img-fashion-brand/ |website=tubefilter |accessdate=6 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nThey were nominated in 2019 for Best YouTube Ensemble at the [[11th Shorty Awards]].<ref name=\"11th_Shorty\">{{cite web |title=Merrell Twins - YouTube Ensemble - The Shorty Awards |url=https://shortyawards.com/11th/merrelltwins |website=shortyawards.com |accessdate=14 February 2020}}</ref> At the [[2020 Kids' Choice Awards]], they were nominated for Favorite Female Social Star.<ref name=\"2020KCA\" />\n\n==Filmography==\n: ''This filmography is of the twins as a duo.''\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Television and Film\n|-\n! Year(s)\n! Title\n! Veronica's role\n! Vanessa's role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2014\u20132016\n| ''[[Jane the Virgin]]''\n| Victoria \n| Valeria\n| 5 episodes\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[Faking It (U.S. TV series)|Faking It]]''\n| Willa \n| Ella \n| Episode: \"Prom Scare\"\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''The Standoff''\n| Mia \n| Maya\n| Direct-to-video film\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Hyperlinked]]''\n| Missy \n| Chrissy \n| Episode: \"The Interview\"\n|-\n|2020\n|''[[Like a Boss (film)|Like A Boss]]''\n|Lola\n|Layla\n|\n|-\n|2022\n|''Switched''\n|N/A\n|Olivia\n|\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Award Show\n! Category\n! Result\n! Refs\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" scope=\"row\" | 2016\n| [[Shorty Awards]]\n| YouNower of the Year\n| {{win}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=\"8th_Shorty\" />\n|-\n| [[Streamy Awards]]\n| Live\n| {{win}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=\"2016Streamy\" />\n|-\n| 2017\n| [[Teen Choice Awards]]\n| Choice Female Web Star\n| {{nominated}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=\"TCA2017\">{{cite web |last1=Vulpo |first1=Mike |title=Teen Choice Awards 2017 Winners: The Complete List |url=https://www.eonline.com/uk/news/873077/teen-choice-awards-2017-winners-the-complete-list |website=E! News |accessdate=14 February 2020}}</ref> \n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" scope=\"row\" | 2018\n| [[Teen Choice Awards]]\n| Choice Female Web Star\n| {{nominated}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=\"EONLINE2018\" />\n|-\n| [[Teen Choice Awards]]\n| Choice Youtuber\n| {{nominated}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=\"EONLINE2018\" />\n|-\n| [[Streamy Awards]]\n| Lifestyle\n| {{win}} \n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=\"2018Streamy\" />\n|-\n| 2019\n| [[Shorty Awards]]\n| Best YouTube Ensemble\n| {{nominated}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=\"11th_Shorty\" />\n|-\n| 2020\n| [[Kids' Choice Awards]]\n| Favorite Female Social Star\n| {{pending}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref name=\"2020KCA\">{{cite web |last1=Petski |first1=Denise |title=\u2018Avengers: Endgame\u2019 Leads Nickelodeon\u2019s Kids\u2019 Choice Awards Nominations; Chance The Rapper Set As Host |url=https://deadline.com/2020/02/avengers-end-game-leads-nickelodeons-kids-choice-awards-nominations-billie-eilish-taylor-swift-chance-the-rapper-full-list-1202859259/ |website=Deadline |accessdate=13 February 2020}}</r